<!DOCTYPE div SYSTEM "../dtd/tei-epidoc.dtd">
<div id="lostcertain" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" lang="en">
    <head>Letters completely lost (extent certain or not certain)</head>
    <div id="lostcertain-typographic" type="gl-typographic">
        <head>Traditional typographic representation</head>
        <list>
            <item><bibl><title level="a" type="abbreviated">Panciera</title>, <abbr expan="page">p.</abbr><biblScope type="pages">18</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><title level="a" type="abbreviated">Donicht</title>, <abbr expan="page">p.</abbr><biblScope type="pages">4</biblScope></bibl>: <list type="ordered">
                    <item>[&#160;&#183;&#160;&#183;&#160;&#183;&#160;]</item>
                    <item>[&#160;&#183;&#160;10&#160;&#183;&#160;]</item>
                    <item> [&#160;&#183;&#160;c.10&#160;&#183;&#160;]</item>
                    <item> [&#160;-&#160;4.2cm&#160;-&#160;]</item>
                    <item lang="en">not addressed</item>
                </list></item>
        </list>
    </div>
    <div id="lostcertain-encoding" type="gl-encoding">
        <head>EpiDoc encoding</head>
        <list type="ordered">
            <item>
                <tag>gap reason="lost" extent="3" unit="character"/</tag>
            </item>
            <item>
                <tag>gap reason="lost" extent="10" unit="character"/</tag>
            </item>
            <item>
                <tag>gap id="gap2" reason="lost" extent="10" unit="character"/</tag><tag>certainty target="gap2" locus="extent" degree="low"/</tag>
            </item>
            <item>
                <tag>gap reason="lost" extent="4.2" unit="cm"/</tag>
            </item>
             <item>
                <tag>gap id="gap3" reason="lost" extent="2" unit="character" /</tag><tag>certainty target="gap3" locus="extent" degree="low" /</tag>
            </item>            
        </list>
    </div>
    <div id="lostcertain-edition" type="gl-edition">
        <head>EpiDoc appearance with standard XSLT</head>
        <list type="ordered">
            <item>
                <gap reason="lost" extent="3" unit="character" />
            </item>
            <item>
                <gap reason="lost" extent="10" unit="character" />
            </item>
            <item>
                <gap id="gap2" reason="lost" extent="10" unit="character" /><certainty target="gap2" locus="extent" degree="low" />
            </item>
            <item>
                <gap reason="lost" extent="4.2" unit="cm" />
            </item>
            <item>
                <gap id="gap3" reason="lost" extent="2" unit="character" /><certainty target="gap3" locus="extent" degree="low" />
            </item>
        </list>
    </div>
    <div id="lostcertain-notes" type="gl-notes">
        <head>Notes</head>
        <list type="ordered">
            <item>The first example indicates the certain loss of exactly 3 characters.</item>
            <item>The second example indicates the certain loss of exactly 10 characters.</item>
            <item>The third example indicates the certain loss of approximately 10 characters.</item>
            <item>The fourth example indicates the certain loss of 4.2cm of text.</item>
            <item>The fifth example indicates the certain loss of exactly 2 characters.</item>
            <item>If a unit of measurement other than "character" is used for the "unit" attribute on <tag>gap</tag>,
                then no <tag>certainty locus="extent" degree="low"</tag> element should be associated with the <tag>gap</tag>.</item>
        </list>
    </div>
    
    <div id="lostcertain-responsibility" type="gl-responsibility">
        <head>Responsibility for this section</head>
        <listBibl>
            <bibl>
                <respStmt>
                    <resp>author</resp>
                    <name>Tom Elliott</name>
                </respStmt>
            </bibl>
        </listBibl>
    </div>
</div>
